techmeme.title: Canada orders the windup of TikTok's Canadian business citing national security risks, and says it's not blocking Canadians' access to the app (Reuters)
Match Group reports Q3 revenue up 2% YoY to $895M, vs. $900.9M est., paying users down 3% to 15.2M, forecasts Q4 revenue below est.; MTCH drops 12%+ after hours (Jaspreet Singh/Reuters)
Lyft reports Q3 revenue up 32% YoY to $1.52B, vs. $1.44B est, gross bookings up 16% to $4.1B, forecasts Q4 gross bookings above est.; LYFT jumps 20% after hours (Akash Sriram/Reuters)
Arm reports Q2 revenue up 5% YoY to $844M, vs. $810.9M est., royalty revenue up 23% to $514M, and forecasts Q3 revenue below estimates (Ian King/Bloomberg)
Qualcomm reports Q4 revenue up 19% YoY to $10.24B, vs. $9.9B est., guides to a strong Q1, and approves $15B in additional buybacks; QCOM jumps 7%+ after hours (Kif Leswing/CNBC)
